What insurance do I need?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the sheep, the marital status, the type of vehicle to be secured or the use of the car, among others.
Having the car is just the beginning.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we have to be clear about what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is embodied in an insurance contract, which provides that the company receives the value of the premium agreed in exchange for being held responsible for the obligation to pay the compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account various factors such as age, sex, age of the sheep, marital status, type of vehicle to ensure or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that more likely to suffer an accident, it is more likely to pay.
That is why both the over 25 and the women have to pay lower premiums, since the statistics reflect that they have a lower rate of sinestrality due to their caution.
In addition, by taking advantage of the accounts, the companies have concluded that married persons tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the probability of having some kind of percussion.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver needs to study the situation well to choose that car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or other insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age face various drawbacks when hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as the low driving experience and the age of the sheep.
Although the ideal to be well insured is a risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can choose a whole risk with franchise, so that they get insurance coverage at all risks but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the customer pays part of the amount of the sinister.
The amount of the customer's money will be pre-established depending on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount, specifies Luis Noguera, maximum responsible in Spain of First Europe, online insurance mediator.
Another option is an extended third party insurance, so that the customer is guaranteed protection from damage caused to third parties, even if not in the face of the causes in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and the loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid the claims as far as possible, as this will have an impact on the bonus, thus reducing the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a charge on that basic fee.
The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year it can be allowed to increase the bonuses - clarify Noguera.
After the 25-year run, drivers have the easiest time to hire a insurance, as the sinestrality rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended is to hire a whole risk with franchise.
‘Youths cannot normally make use of the experience they have acquired before being used in an accident, and even at driving time,’ says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of driving, once already the ‘feed of the novice’.
